<task id="task_F7D69D4BA9FD47B1B37A2BB0AEFE9C3C">
  <title>Pushing a Winner</title>
  <shortdesc>The winner is the experience that achieved the best results during
	 your test. One experience is designated as the winner. However, you can push
	 any experience, even if it is not the designated experience. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <taskbody>
    <context id="context_D5734D1E47D445C8B073331765941993">
      <p>Pushing a winner creates a new campaign with only one experience and
		  any targeting conditions required. After you approve this new campaign and
		  deactivate the original test, the winning content displays to everyone on your
		  site. If different experiences win for each segment, push each winner. The
		  appropriate targeting is enabled to ensure that members of each segment see the
		  winning content. Remember to deactivate the original test. 
		</p>
    </context>
    <steps id="steps_0650F83C84B54FB884750BD336AF17F9">
      <step id="step_761684707BE24BB8B4FC9A4EF283505F">
        <cmd>Click 
			 <uicontrol>Push Winner</uicontrol> next to the winning experience (or
			 experiences when using the segment filters). 
		  </cmd>
        <stepresult></stepresult>
      </step>
    </steps>
  </taskbody>
